## Question 22

`mv potter.txt Potter_story.txt`
This command changes the pathing and because you are not moving the original file location it instead changes the name of the file. If the command was `mv potter.txt MBB101`, the file would just be moved to the external folder MBB101

## Question 23

`ln -s modified/Potter_story.txt` creates a symbolic link using the clarifier modified after the ln -s, therefore making the path to the file then read Potter_story.txt -> modified/Potter_story.txt

## Question 24

ls -l displays the symbolic link by saying Potter_story.txt -> modified/Potter_story.txt where previously it just would have said Potter_story.txt
